 Install PostgreSQL Client (if not already installed)
In your Docker container:
bash# Update package list
apt update

# Install PostgreSQL client
apt install -y postgresql-client

Connect to Our Database
bashpsql -h [MAT'S_IP_ADDRESS] -p 5432 -U postgres -d chaos_cooking

Replace [MAT'S_IP_ADDRESS] with the actual IP I'll provide
Enter Password

When prompted, enter: Password82
You should see: chaos_cooking=#

Test the Connection
sql-- See all our users
SELECT * FROM users;

-- See available recipes  
SELECT title, description FROM recipes;

-- See leftover ingredients
SELECT name, category FROM ingredients WHERE category LIKE 'leftover%';

-- Exit when done
\q
Use in Your Code
Now you can write hard-coded queries in your application using:
Connection: postgresql://postgres:Password82@[MAT'S_IP_ADDRESS]:5432/chaos_cooking

* My machine has to be running for you to access the connection to the database*

Let me know if you encounter issues!